     <div type="sonnet">
   <pb facs="11"/>
   <head>A Sonet to the Author.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>THe faire &amp; comly cariage,</l>
      <l>Being daughter of the court of Kings:</l>
      <l>Is found in <hi>Galateo</hi> sage,</l>
      <l>Whose great renowne, &amp; valour rings.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>I suck from hence, the courtly milke,</l>
      <l>Of faire, sweet, gentle, lordly port:</l>
      <l>Hither may th' quaintest cloath'd in silk,</l>
      <l>For counsell come, and hav't in short.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Heere he presents in patterns rare,</l>
      <l>Instructions for thee to receive,</l>
      <l>That without paine, thou mayst take care,</l>
      <l>Thy selfe from errors to relieve.</l>
   </lg>
</div>
